cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the development of a system for searching, constructing, exploring, and discussing web archive collections. The system is designed to support collaborative construction and exploration of these collections. The paper focuses on the functionalities of the current prototype and feedback from archiving organizations. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Digital Libraries (cs.DL), as the paper deals with the organization and retrieval of digital content. Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) is also likely, as the paper discusses the design and development of a system for user interaction. Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computers and Society (cs.CY) are less likely but still possible, as the paper touches on the discussion of web content and its preservation for future exploration and analysis.
